    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "For reference, another project which has considered this issue: https://github.com/liftoff/GateOne/issues/68\n\nThe easiest way to get half-way would be for our default http and https ports to be _different_, such that most users trying to access via http would be on 8888, while https would be on 9999.  Then https mode could run a tiny http server on 8888 that does nothing but redirect to the https url.  I don't know how many cases that would actually catch, though.\n"
